    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-10-18T20:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-10-18T20:36:00-05:00" n="1183"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1183">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/5276.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-18T19:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 18, 1912—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>On account of general excitement of people here over her supposed mission,
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs strongly urged me to request Department not to
                    allow <hi rend="italic">Des Moines</hi> to enter port of Vera Cruz for the
                    present. I replied that I would transmit his request.</p>
                <p>In view of my remonstrances there will be no bombardment ox city, but opposing
                    forces will engage outside.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schuyler.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
